    • Method Detail

      • addEntry

        public void addEntry(ChronoIdentifier identifier)
        Adds the given identifier to the commit timestamp map.

        It will have null associated as commit metadata. If a commit metadata object already exists for that timestamp, the metadata will be kept and will not be overwritten with null.

        Parameters:
        identifier - The ChronoIdentifier to add to the commit map. Must not be null.

      • addEntry

        public void addEntry(java.lang.String branch,
                     long timestamp,
                     java.lang.Object metadata)
        Adds the given commit timestamp (and metadata) to this map.
        Parameters:
        branch - The name of the branch on which the commit occurred. Must not be null.
        timestamp - The timestamp at which the commit occurred. Must not be negative.
        metadata - The metadata associated with the branch. May be null.

      • getContainedBranches

        public java.util.Set<java.lang.String> getContainedBranches()
        Returns the set of branch names for which commits are available.
        Returns:
        Returns an unmodifiable view on the set of branches which have commits assigned to them in this map. Never null.

      • getCommitMetadataForBranch

        public java.util.SortedMap<java.lang.Long,java.lang.Object> getCommitMetadataForBranch(java.lang.String branchName)
        Returns the commit timestamps (and associated metadata) for the given branch.

        The keys of the map are the commit timestamps, the values are the metadata associated with the commit (which may be null).

        Parameters:
        branchName - The name of the branch to get the commits for. Must not be null.
        Returns:
        An unmodifiable view on the map from timestamp to commit metadata for the given branch. May be empty, but never null.
